# Smart Healthcare System – Tinkercad Simulation

This project is fully simulated on **Autodesk Tinkercad Circuits**.  
Click the link below to view, run, and modify the simulation online:

🔗 [View Tinkercad Simulation](https://www.tinkercad.com/things/3m9aOPG0xmg/editel?returnTo=%2Fdashboard%2Fdesigns%2Fcircuits&sharecode=1sdJCGsntPMFY5oXSj5l7EjoWWzN1sQ5Iwap5dbECIw)

---

## 🛠️ Components Used in Simulation
- Arduino Uno
- TMP36 Temperature Sensor
- Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04)
- PIR Motion Sensor
- Potentiometer (Blood Pressure Simulation)
- I2C LCD (16x2)
- Buzzer

---

## 📟 Features in Simulation
- 🌡️ **Temperature Monitoring** – detects fever condition  
- 📏 **Social Distancing** – ultrasonic sensor alerts if distance < 60 cm  
- 🏃 **Motion Detection** – PIR sensor triggers motion alerts  
- 💓 **Heart Rate Simulation** – random values between 70–100 BPM  
- 🩺 **Blood Pressure Simulation** – potentiometer mapped to systolic/diastolic values  
- 🔔 **Buzzer Alerts** – triggered for fever, close distance, or motion  
- 📺 **LCD Display** – real-time vitals in compact format  

---

💡 *Tip: You can clone this circuit in Tinkercad and try adding more sensors like SpO₂, humidity, or Wi-Fi for IoT logging.*
